{
  "texts": [
    "Each iteration counts all possible pairwise combinations of the newly merged symbols to add the most frequently used combinations to the growing vocabulary.",
    "Figure 2 shows a simple example that begins with a base vocabulary containing byte codes that represent each letter of the standard English alphabet a through z.",
    "Each cell in the matrix contains the co-occurrence frequency of the symbol pairs in the TFD developed from a training corpus.",
    "The highest frequency occurrence in this example is the symbol pair representing the letters o and f which is the 2-gram word of.",
    "The algorithm adds a new symbol representing the 2-gram of to update the current vocabulary."
  ]
}